          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1706632481707-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> roughly</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>chickpeas</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1706632500650-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1706632500650-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1706632500650-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1706632500650-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1706632500650-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened slightly, add the<strong> chopped tomato</strong> to the pan with your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>harissa paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>ras el hanout </strong>and<strong> half </strong>your<strong> ginger & garlic paste </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Stir it all together and cook for 1 min or until fragrant, then add the <strong>cooked butternut squash cubes </strong>with the<strong> drained chickpeas</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, then stir it all together and reduce the heat to medium for 3-4 min until thickened – this is your <strong>Moroccan-style squash stew</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1706632505982-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1706632505982-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1706632505982-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1706632505982-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1706632505982-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, squeeze your pouch[es] of <strong>cooked brown long grain rice </strong>to separate the grains</p><p>Tear the top corner of the pouch[es] (just a little!) and <strong>microwave</strong> for 2 min or until piping hot</p><p>Tip: If you're cooking two or more pouches, pop them in together but increase the microwave cook time accordingly</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1706632510401-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1706632510401-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1706632510401-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1706632510401-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1706632510401-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander & parsley</strong> roughly</p><p>Add your <strong>cultured coconut</strong> to a bowl with the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lemon wedges</strong>, the remaining <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped coriander & parsley</strong> to the bowl and stir it all together – this is your <strong>herby coconut yoghurt</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1706632515878-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1706632515878-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1706632515878-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1706632515878-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1706632515878-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> Moroccan-style squash stew</strong> over the<strong> cooked brown rice</strong> with a dollop of <strong>herby coconut yoghurt</strong> and a <strong>lemon wedge</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with your<strong> flaked almonds</strong> and <strong>remaining chopped coriander & parsley</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
